azel\">{{cite book|last1=Hazel|first1=John|title=John W. Hazel's Book of Records|date=1977|publisher=D Winter & Son|location=Dundee|page=48}}</ref>}}\n{{Election box candidate unopposed with party link|\n|party=Liberal Party (UK)\n|candidate=[[John Leng (politician)|John Leng]]\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link no swing|\n|winner=Liberal Party (UK)\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Elections in the 1890s===\n[[File:Sir John Leng.jpg|thumb|120px|Leng]]\n{{Election box begin|title=[[1892 United Kingdom general election|General election 1892]]: Dundee (2 seats) <ref name=\"ReferenceCraig85-18\"/><ref>Whitaker's Almanack, 1893</ref>}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party=Liberal Party (UK)\n|candidate=[[John Leng (politician)|John Leng]]\n|votes=8,484\n|percentage=30.5\n|change= &minus;4.7\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party=Liberal Party (UK)\n|candidate=[[Edmund Robertson, 1st Baron Lochee|Edmund Robertson]]\n|votes=8,191\n|percentage=29.5\n|change= &minus;5.8\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party=Conservative Party (UK)\n|candidate=[[William Dalgleish]]\n|votes=5,659\n|percentage=20.4\n|change= +5.2\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party=Liberal Unionist Party \n|candidate=[[William Charles Smith (politician)|William Charles Smith]]\n|votes=5,066\n|percentage=18.3\n|change= +4.0\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party= Scottish Labour Party (1888)\n|candidate=[[James MacDonald (trade unionist)|James MacDonald]]\n|votes=354\n|percentage=1.3\n|change= ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n|votes=2,532\n|percentage=9.1\n|change= &minus;10.9\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n|votes= 14,025 (est)\n|percentage=77.0\n|change= +8.7\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n |reg. electors = 18,214\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n|winner=Liberal Party (UK)\n|swing= &minus;5.0\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n|winner=Liberal Party (UK)\n|swing= &minus;5.5\n}}\n{{Election box